messages.message:
I was just reviewing UI text for rule-based classification and realized we could clean up how we refer to *custom functions*.

I would love to see us follow a consistent naming scheme, like:
• classification function
• splitting function
• extraction function
• cleaning function
• validation function
• integration function
...or same as above but with a "custom" prefix (i.e., custom classification function). I leave it up to more technical folks whether we need the "custom".

Screenshots in thread of existing inconsistencies. It'd be great to fix this, either in conjunction with heuristic classification or as a separate effort. @Kaustubh (KD) @Natasha @Serena

Great idea!! :raised_hands:

I don’t think we need the word “custom”, but not a strong opinion
Yeah agree with all of the above
We should be able to change this during the heuristic classification effort right @Serena
